    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="791"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d791">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/225</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Lend-Lease Administrator</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-11">February 11,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Stettinius</hi>: In view of the efforts which
                    the Turkish Government is now making to prepare for the possible extension of
                    hostilities in the Near East during the spring, the Department of State regards
                    it as particularly important that supplies be furnished to <pb facs="0690"
                        n="678" xml:id="pg_678"/> Turkey as soon as possible, not only for the
                    purpose of strengthening the Turkish Government in its announced determination
                    to resist aggression but also in order to enable that resistance to be
                    effective.</p>
                <p>This Department understands that the Turkish military authorities consider it of
                    the greatest importance, for instance, that 950 trucks, for which the Turkish
                    Government has already deposited more than $1,000,000 in cash payment, reach
                    Turkey by the end of March.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sumner Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
